ure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6644818/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/6644822/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">Figs. 1–21</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1860,2031]" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1860,1886]" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">Description.</emphasis>
Color pattern of anterior dorsum and face as in 
<figureCitation box="[836,943,1860,1886]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 1–4" captionStart-1="FIGURES 5–8" captionStartId-0="4.[151,264,1887,1911]" captionStartId-1="5.[151,264,1322,1346]" captionTargetBox-0="[163,1424,786,1855]" captionTargetBox-1="[160,1428,189,1291]" captionTargetId-0="figure-271@4.[151,1436,777,1864]" captionTargetId-1="figure-17@5.[151,1436,181,1298]" captionTargetPageId-0="4" captionTargetPageId-1="5" captionText-0="FIGURES 1–4. Japananoides circularis sp. nov. 1. ♂, dorsal view; 2. ♂, lateral view; 3. ♂, Head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. ♂, face." captionText-1="FIGURES 5–8. Japananoides circularis sp. nov. 5. ♀, dorsal view; 6. ♀, lateral view; 7. ♀, Head and thorax, dorsal view; 8. ♀, face." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6644814" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6644816" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6644814/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6644816/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">Figs. 1–8</figureCitation>
. Crown with a white median preapical spot. Male face dark brown with four incomplete transverse white stripes (
<figureCitation box="[919,988,1896,1922]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[163,1424,786,1855]" captionTargetId="figure-271@4.[151,1436,777,1864]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Japananoides circularis sp. nov. 1. ♂, dorsal view; 2. ♂, lateral view; 3. ♂, Head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. ♂, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6644814" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6644814/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); female face dark brown with six white stripes (
<figureCitation box="[240,308,1932,1958]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–8" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1322,1346]" captionTargetBox="[160,1428,189,1291]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[151,1436,181,1298]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5–8. Japananoides circularis sp. nov. 5. ♀, dorsal view; 6. ♀, lateral view; 7. ♀, Head and thorax, dorsal view; 8. ♀, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6644816" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6644816/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1860,2031]" box="[199,743,1968,1995]" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">Other external features as in generic description.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1860,2031]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,429]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="351" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">
<emphasis box="[199,370,2004,2030]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Aedeagus shafts each with three (
<typeStatus box="[744,855,2004,2030]" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">paratypes</typeStatus>
) or four (
<typeStatus box="[958,1058,2004,2030]" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus box="[1110,1219,2005,2031]" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">paratypes</typeStatus>
) lamellar subapical processes; gonopore subapical (
<figureCitation box="[511,650,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–15" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[152,1426,464,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-128@6.[151,1436,453,1857]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 9–15. Japananoides circularis sp. nov. 9. Male genital capsule, lateral view; 10. Valve, ventral view; 11. Subgenital plates, ventral view; 12. Aedeagus, ventral view; 13. Aedeagus,left lateral view; 14. Connective, ventral view; 15. Style, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6644818" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6644818/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="351">Figs. 12, 13</figureCitation>
). Connective with arms shorter than stem (
<figureCitation box="[1142,1226,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–15" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[152,1426,464,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-128@6.[151,1436,453,1857]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 9–15. Japananoides circularis sp. nov. 9. Male genital capsule, lateral view; 10. Valve, ventral view; 11. Subgenital plates, ventral view; 12. Aedeagus, ventral view; 13. Aedeagus,left lateral view; 14. Connective, ventral view; 15. Style, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6644818" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6644818/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="351">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Style broad with slightly laterally curved caudal apex of apophysis, with small subapical setae (
<figureCitation box="[1029,1112,186,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–15" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[152,1426,464,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-128@6.[151,1436,453,1857]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 9–15. Japananoides circularis sp. nov. 9. Male genital capsule, lateral view; 10. Valve, ventral view; 11. Subgenital plates, ventral view; 12. Aedeagus, ventral view; 13. Aedeagus,left lateral view; 14. Connective, ventral view; 15. Style, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6644818" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6644818/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="351">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="351">
Female pygofer with ventroposterior margin sharply incurved (
<figureCitation box="[934,1021,223,250]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[161,1417,194,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[153,1435,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. Japananoides circularis sp. nov. 16. Female genital capsule, lateral view; 17. seventh sternite, ventral view; 18. First valvula, lateral view; 19. Detail of sculptures of first valvula; 20. Second valvula, lateral view; 21. Detail of sculptures of second valaula." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6644822" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6644822/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="351">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). Female seventh sternum posterior margin with deep angulate median concavity, posterolateral margins acutely produced (
<figureCitation box="[1152,1238,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[161,1417,194,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[153,1435,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. Japananoides circularis sp. nov. 16. Female genital capsule, lateral view; 17. seventh sternite, ventral view; 18. First valvula, lateral view; 19. Detail of sculptures of first valvula; 20. Second valvula, lateral view; 21. Detail of sculptures of second valaula." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6644822" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6644822/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="351">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
). First valvula of ovipositor slightly curved, attenuate to apex, with obscure reticulate sculpture dorsally and scale-like sculpture ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[226,362,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[161,1417,194,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[153,1435,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. Japananoides circularis sp. nov. 16. Female genital capsule, lateral view; 17. seventh sternite, ventral view; 18. First valvula, lateral view; 19. Detail of sculptures of first valvula; 20. Second valvula, lateral view; 21. Detail of sculptures of second valaula." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6644822" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6644822/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="351">Figs. 18, 19</figureCitation>
). Second valvula with few large rounded teeth on distal half of dorsal margin (
<figureCitation box="[1242,1379,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[161,1417,194,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[153,1435,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. Japananoides circularis sp. nov. 16. Female genital capsule, lateral view; 17. seventh sternite, ventral view; 18. First valvula, lateral view; 19. Detail of sculptures of first valvula; 20. Second valvula, lateral view; 21. Detail of sculptures of second valaula." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6644822" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6644822/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="351">Figs. 20, 21</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,429]" box="[199,1054,366,393]" pageId="6" pageNumber="351">
